how do i escape a really bad kink in the neck yesterday i got this bad kink in my neck and i couldn't even move my neck cause it hurt is there any exercises to get rid of it what you seem to be describing is what is known as a torticollis or wry neck often from sleeping in a poor position poor sitting position at computer etc assuming you have no bad symptoms loss of power sensation to your upper limbs etc then these things often resolve of their own accord within a few days you can take some simple analgesia use deep heat compresses or hot bath and try to relax to reduce the tension in your neck you can move your neck to the limits of the pain but do not force anything as it will only get worse slow movements in the opposite direction to the kink and also in a circular motion at the end of the day it will still take a few days to resolve but be patient Equine conformation Massage Urinary incontinence Carpal tunnel syndrome Repetitive strain injury Chronic fatigue syndrome Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Pain Weight training Out-of-body experience First aid Myocardial infarction Epidural Professional wrestling holds Migraine Fibromyalgia Torticollis Glossary of partner dance terms Traumatic brain injury Tai Chi Chuan Hypnosis Stroke Balance disorder Alexander Technique Osteoarthritis Diving Poliomyelitis Medicine Childbirth Cancer Rheumatoid arthritis Sleep apnea Professional wrestling throws Multiple sclerosis Hyperthermia Narcolepsy Prostate cancer Angina Restless legs syndrome Anatomical terms of location Trumpet Professional wrestling slang Analgesic Radiation therapy Insomnia Euthanasia Snake Breastfeeding Electromagnetic field Apoplexy Essential tremor Swingout Seismic retrofit Reflexology Back pain Diving suit Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Thoracic outlet syndrome The Kinks Tension headache Milton H. Erickson Aikido Internal ballistics Diabetes mellitus Diazepam Transverse myelitis Manual transmission Anesthesia Paracetamol Anxiety Common cold Chiropractic Planetary o